12.22.19  10:08 am   I'm the one who asked about midi keyboards a couple months ago. I realized that the reason I'm unsure about getting one is that there are a lot of people who just click in notes and make perfectly good music that way. what do you think about that? is it just something that varies from person to person? I still think a keyboard could be an invaluable tool for quickly sketching out ideas for me though, given my short attention span, so I suppose I'll just have to try it myself.
bonus question: does capitalizing only "I" make me narcissistic? I just realized it's something I do

     computer keyboards are not volume sensitive. so, if you think you have any inclinations resembling anything like dancing or drumming, or grooving out in any sort of way, or if you would like to actually 'play' anything, then the music keyboard is going to be an avenue that will allow you to definitely express this to the computer in a real way
